<DOCUMENT source-infobase-name="Rules" content-collection-id="NYCrules" source-infobase-title="The Rules of the City of New York" base-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\" default-split-level="Chapter" makefile-filename="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\NYCrules.mak" css-stylesheet-href="#!-- #ID=NYCrules_css_id --#" xml-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\XML\" css-stylesheet-name="NYCrules_css" makefile-document-depth="2">
	<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-477" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-97842" number="35939" version="148">
			<HEADING>Chapter 44: Standard Test Procedures to Determine Smoke Emissions from Generators with an Output of 40 kw or More</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-4043" name="T15C044"/>Chapter 44: Standard Test Procedures to Determine Smoke Emissions from Generators with an Output of 40 kw or More</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-480" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Subtitle" style-name-escaped="Subtitle" style-id="0-0-0-15301" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-483" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Subpart" style-name-escaped="Subpart" style-id="0-0-0-15960" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-30757" number="35940" version="3">
								<HEADING>§ 44-01 Definitions.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-4045" name="T15C044_44-01"/>§ 44-01 Definitions.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30758" number="35941" version="3">
									<PARA>&quot;<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Generator</CHARFORMAT>&quot; means any internal combustion engine that operates as a mechanical or electrical power source. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30759" number="35942" version="3">
									<PARA>&quot;<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Kilowatt</CHARFORMAT>&quot; means a unit of electrical power equal to one thousand watts. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30761" number="35943" version="174">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 12/5/2016, eff. 1/4/2017) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-98272" number="35944" version="174">
								<HEADING>§ 44-02 Test Procedures.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-4047" name="T15C044_44-02"/>§ 44-02 Test Procedures.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30762" number="35945" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Exemptions.</CHARFORMAT> The following generators are not subject to this rule&apos;s testing requirements: Generators that are (1) certified Tier IV as set forth in table one of 40 C.F.R. § 1039.101 or any subsequent United States environmental protection agency, and (2) newly installed and being registered for the first time. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30763" number="35946" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Test Procedures.</CHARFORMAT> All generators that are subject to the test requirements of this rule must be tested in accordance with the procedures set forth in paragraph (1) or (2) below. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30764" number="35947" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Stack Test Procedure.</CHARFORMAT>&#160;<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30765" number="35948" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Generators must meet equivalent Tier IV particulate matter (PM) emissions standards established by the United States Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) as set forth in table one of 40 C.F.R. § 1039.101 or any subsequent United States EPA emissions standard for such generator that is at least as stringent. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30766" number="35949" version="1175">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>In order to demonstrate that the PM emissions from the stack of a generator meet the Tier IV PM emissions standard, testing must be performed by the equipment owner following EPA Method 5, titled &quot;Determination of particulate matter emissions from stationary sources&quot; (Appendix A-3 to 40 C.F.R. Part 60). The P.E. or R.A, must certify the stack test results. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30767" number="35950" version="1175">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Smoke Test Procedure.</CHARFORMAT> A smoke test on a generator shall be performed in accordance with the procedures set forth in EPA Method 9, titled &quot;Visual determination of the opacity of emissions from stationary sources&quot; (Appendix A-4 to 40 C.F.R. Part 60). The test results shall indicate less than 20 percent opacity for any two consecutive minutes in any 60-minute period. The smoke test must be performed and certified by a qualified visible emissions evaluator. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30768" number="35951" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Recordkeeping.</CHARFORMAT>&#160;<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30769" number="35952" version="2297">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>For generators that require a registration under § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="24-109" destination-id="0-0-0-0">24-109</LINK> of the Administrative Code (those stationary generators with an output from 40 kw to less than 450 kw and all emergency and portable generators with an output of 40 kw or greater), proof that the generator passed either a stack test using EPA Method 5 or a smoke test using EPA Method 9 must be submitted to the department upon request. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30770" number="35953" version="2297">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>For generators that require a certificate of operation under § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="24-122" destination-id="0-0-0-0">24-122</LINK> of the Administrative Code (those with an output of 450 kw or more), proof that the generator passed either a stack test using EPA Method 5 or a smoke test using EPA Method 9 must be submitted to the department with the application for an original inspection request to obtain the Certificate of Operation. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30771" number="35954" version="3">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(3)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Records of tests required by this rule shall be maintained by the equipment owner for five years. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-30772" number="35955" version="174">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 12/5/2016, eff. 1/4/2017) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-008]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
					</LEVEL>
				</LEVEL>
			</LEVEL>
		</LEVEL>
	</LEVEL>
</DOCUMENT>